@startuml
title await_reply suspend/resume sequence

actor User
participant "Sniffer" as S
participant "CoWorker" as W
database "DB (schedules)" as DB
participant "DagExecutor" as X
participant "Mailer" as M

== Compose & Await ==
User -> W: due schedule picked (compose)
W -> X: run DAG
X -> M: send trends email (includes [PIPELINE #id])
X -> DB: request_reschedule (RUNNING, due_at+timeout)
note right: context._dag.waiting_node=wait_reply\ncontext._dag.resume_next=[ingest_reply]
X --> W: suspend

== Resume by reply ==
User -> S: email reply (subject contains token)
S -> DB: find RUNNING schedule by pipeline_id
S -> DB: update context._resume.event, due_at=now

== Executor resumes ==
W -> DB: pick due (RUNNING)
W -> X: run DAG (resume)
note right: executor marks waiting node or predecessors as completed
X -> X: continue at ingest_reply
X -> DB: ingest_draft_mail -> drafts.create
X -> DB: mark DONE, clear _resume
X --> W: success

@enduml


